The paper deals with social choice theory, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). It also involves the measurement of beliefs and opinions, which can be related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of logical implications and the examination of different methods can be linked to the subfield of logic in computer science (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the ranking of options, which can be related to the subfield of data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on social attributes and the measurement of opinions can be linked to the subfield of social and information networks (cs.SI).
